---
description: Core project behavior for the Bank Churn Cursor Bootcamp
alwaysApply: true
---

Before making significant changes:
- Read `README.md`
- Read `AGENTS.md`
- Read `docs/03_success_criteria.md`
- Read the relevant task file in `docs/`

Always:
- Propose a short plan before implementing
- Keep changes modular and readable
- Reuse the existing project structure
- Validate outputs against the success criteria
- Pin dependency versions exactly in `requirements.txt` when adding or updating libraries
- Create the project virtual environment before running project code if `.venv` does not exist yet
- Keep `requirements.txt` aligned with the real dependencies used by the project

Never:
- Invent data, metrics, or conclusions
- Create alternative top-level directories
- Ignore missing data or possible data leakage
- Mix exploratory notebook code with reusable production logic

Directory rules:
- Raw data goes in `data/raw/`
- Processed data goes in `data/processed/`
- Reusable code goes in `src/`
- Models go in `artifacts/models/`
- Predictions go in `artifacts/predictions/`
- Logs go in `artifacts/logs/`
- Figures and tables go in `reports/`
- Streamlit app code goes in `app/`